<Layout title={title}>
  <script async src="https://cpwebassets.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js"
  ></script>
  <p>
    A CSS flex box is an essential building block of HTML layouts, as it can
    create rows or columns and transition between the two.
  </p>

  <p>First, add a div with a class name of "flex" to your HTML:</p>

  <Code code={`<div class="flex"></div>`} lang="html" />

  <p>In your CSS, we'll add a class called 'flex':</p>
  <Code code={`.flex{ display: flex; }`} lang="css" />
  <p>
    Using a class to handle a specific property like this is often called a
    "utility" class. Instead of baking the behavior into a specific layout
    element, we can tag anything we want to behave with this simple selector.
  </p>
  <p>
    Now, any child elements you add to this container will behave as columns.
    For instance, to create a two-column layout:
  </p>
  <Code
    code={`<div class="flex">
  <div>1</div>
  <div>2</div>
</div>`}
    lang="html"
  />

